Let me check what the specific error is by looking more closely at the code. I've identified the bug in the BrentSolver.java file. In the `solve(double min, double max)` method, when we return an endpoint that is already a root (has value close to 0), the code has:

```java
// return the first endpoint if it is good enough
double yMin = f.value(min);
if (Math.abs(yMin) <= functionValueAccuracy) {
    setResult(yMin, 0);  // BUG: should be setResult(min, 0)
    return result;
}

// return the second endpoint if it is good enough
double yMax = f.value(max);
if (Math.abs(yMax) <= functionValueAccuracy) {
    setResult(yMax, 0);  // BUG: should be setResult(max, 0)
    return result;
